let's look again at the Java code: In Java:

result = (B-1)/(A-1);

amari = (B-1) % (A-1); if (amari ! =0) result +=1;

So in Fortran, perhaps we can write directly:

result = (B-1)/(A-1)

amari = mod(B-1, A-1) if (amari /=0) then

  result = result + 1

end if

So perhaps temp is not needed.
